review_blob: Can; Appearance: deep dark, small head; Aroma: dark chocolate, roasted coffee, caramel; Taste: sour, bitter; Palate: watery, zero carbonation; Overall: to impress yes, to drink regarly no;

On tap at Stupavar pub; Aroma: Cascade hops, piney, resin, orange; Taste: great bitterness, orange, piney, fruity, malty; Palate: medium body, nice carbonation, thick; Overall: Best APA I had so far from Slovak/Czech Republic, easy to drink, nice and smooth. Well done.

Bottled; Appearance: golden, hazy, minimal head; Aroma: ripe banana dipped in fried butter, dough, clove; Taste: clove, barnyard, light sweetness, grassy; Palate: medium body, thick feel, lively; Overall: Very good complex weizen;

Bottled; Aroma: slight hops, slight malt, raisin brioche; Appearance: amber, clear, minimal head; Taste: light sweetness, lightly bitter, malty; Palate: light body, sticky, soft carbonation, bitter finish; Overall: Good beer to enjoy over night;

Bottled; Appearance: Orange, hazy, thick beautiful head; Aroma: Ripe pineapple, tangerine, hops. resin; Taste: medium sweetness, medium bitterness, piney, citrusy; Palate: medium body, sticky, soft carbonation, bitter refreshing finish; Nice beer

On tap at Starometianska pivotka; Appearance: Dark amber; Aroma: shy notes of coffee beans in chocolate, cereal, caramel; Taste: lightly sour, light sweetness, unpleasant bitterness; Palate: rough, light body, thin texture, average carbonation, bitter finish; Overall: Maybe it should rest a bit more, in current state not very drinkable;

On tap at Starometianska pivotka; Appearance: Dark amber, thick yellowish foam; Aroma: Malty, canned sweet pineapple, caramel, sweet tropical fruit, candies, slight grapefruit; Taste: medium sweetness with beautiful transition to bitterness, piney, caramel; Palate: full body, oily sticky texture, soft carbonation, long bitter finish; The only conspiracy I believe in! Great beer.

Bottled; Aroma: Malty sweet; Appearance: Great foam, deep dark colour; Taste: heavy cloying sweetness, no bitterness, insignificant; Palate: Light body, thin texture, fizzy, no finish; Not recommended in bottle;

Bottled. Aroma: caramel, citrus, chocolate, pines; appearance: slight foam, dark black; taste: liquorice, malty sweet to hoppy bitter, great balance; palate: full body, oily, soft carbon, bitter and persistent finish; overall: great beer, american hops suits the dark style well, alcohol is also suitable, great to sip slowly and contemplate

On tap: Urban House Bratislava
Colour: Dark amber
Aroma: Malt, molasses, flowers, honey, caramel
Taste: Very bitter, significant hops, some coffee
Aftertaste: Persistent bitterness on the palate
Overall: Well, first look, first sniff and first sip is pretty good, but then you start to feel that the makers tried to do something very good but slipped into the waters of mediocre. Still, the opinions differ, so try it out.

Appearance: classic pale ale/lager

Aroma: malty, semi sweet, sort of floral, overall pleasant
Taste: not very bitter, malty, pleasant for night drinking
Finish: malty, not persistent on the palate
Overall: forgetable, but enjoyable
